Clifford Chance Raises Pay for Salaried Lawyers With Experience

-- B y   L i n d s a y   F o r t a d o
-- 
2011-06-07T13:58:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/clifford-chance-raises-pay-for-salaried-lawyers-with-experience.html
Clifford Chance LLP, the largest U.K.
law firm by revenue, is increasing salaries for lawyers in its
 London  office with at least one year of experience and paying
bonuses of as much as 40 percent.  The firm will pay lawyers with a year’s experience 68,500
pounds ($112,600), up from 68,000 pounds last year, and a bonus
of as much as 20,550 pounds, the firm said in an e-mailed
statement today. Salaries for lawyers two years out of training
will rise to 75,000 pounds, plus a maximum bonus of 22,500
pounds. Lawyers with three years’ experience will get 85,500
pounds with a bonus as high as 25,650 pounds.  Lawyers with four years or more experience qualify for
bonuses as high as 40 percent, the firm said. Their salary
levels are confidential.  Salaries for lawyers at  Clifford Chance  who are in training
and those that have just completed training will stay the same,
at 38,000 pounds, 43,000 pounds and 61,500 pounds, the firm
said.  To contact the reporter for this story:
Lindsay Fortado in London
at   lfortado@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 